Two people died while 13 others were injured after a taxi overturned near Umzimkhulu in KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday morning. According to the KwaZulu-Natal Emergency Medical Services spokesperson, Rob McKenzie, paramedics treated the injured people at the scene. McKenzie said they were treated for injuries ranging from serious to critical before being transported to nearby hospitals for further care. “The exact cause of the crash is not known at this stage and it is going to be investigated by the police,” said McKenzie.